<section xmlns="http://xml.house.gov/schemas/uslm/1.0" style="-uslm-lc:I80" id="idbf938521-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa" identifier="/us/usc/t42/s12655a"><num value="12655a">§ 12655a.</num><heading> Limitation on purchase of capital equipment</heading><content>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I11" class="indent0">Not to exceed 10 percent of the amount of assistance made available to a program agency under this division shall be used for the purchase of major capital equipment.</p>
</content><sourceCredit id="idbf938522-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">(<ref href="/us/pl/101/610/tI/s199B">Pub. L. 101–610, title I, § 199B</ref>, formerly § 122, <date date="1990-11-16">Nov. 16, 1990</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/104/3140">104 Stat. 3140</ref>; <ref href="/us/pl/102/10/s5/2">Pub. L. 102–10, § 5(2)</ref>, <date date="1991-03-12">Mar. 12, 1991</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/105/30">105 Stat. 30</ref>; renumbered § 199B and amended <ref href="/us/pl/103/82/tI/s101/a">Pub. L. 103–82, title I, § 101(a)</ref>, (e)(3), <date date="1993-09-21">Sept. 21, 1993</date>, <ref href="/us/stat/107/788">107 Stat. 788</ref>, 815.)</sourceCredit>
<notes type="uscNote" id="idbf938523-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa">
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="editorialNotes" id="idbf938524-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Editorial Notes</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I76" topic="codification" id="idbf938525-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Codification</heading>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Section was formerly classified to <ref href="/us/usc/t42/s12542">section 12542 of this title</ref> prior to renumbering by <ref href="/us/pl/103/82/s101/a">Pub. L. 103–82, § 101(a)</ref>.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="amendments" id="idbf938526-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Amendments</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1993—<ref href="/us/pl/103/82/s101/e/3">Pub. L. 103–82, § 101(e)(3)</ref>, amended section generally, substituting provisions relating to limitation on purchase of capital equipment for provisions relating to allocation of funds.</p>
<p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">1991—Subsec. (e). <ref href="/us/pl/102/10">Pub. L. 102–10</ref> inserted “service” after “youth”.</p>
</note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" role="crossHeading" topic="statutoryNotes" id="idbf938527-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered"><b>Statutory Notes and Related Subsidiaries</b></heading></note>
<note style="-uslm-lc:I74" topic="effectiveDateOfAmendment" id="idbf938528-3a70-11f1-ae07-e4213316b5fa"><heading class="centered smallCaps">Effective Date of 1993 Amendment</heading><p style="-uslm-lc:I21" class="indent0">Amendment by <ref href="/us/pl/103/82">Pub. L. 103–82</ref> effective <date date="1993-10-01">Oct. 1, 1993</date>, see <ref href="/us/pl/103/82/s123">section 123 of Pub. L. 103–82</ref>, set out as a note under <ref href="/us/usc/t16/s1701">section 1701 of Title 16</ref>, Conservation.</p>
</note>
</notes>
